	<div class="the_hub_content_wrapper the_hub_article">
		<div class="the_hub_content">
		<a href="/category/the-hub/" class="header_link">
		<div class="the_hub_title_wrapper">
			<div class="the_hub_logo">
				<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lb-content-widgets/img/lit-horn.svg">
			</div>
			<div class="the_hub_title">
				<h1>The Hub</h1>
			</div>
			<div class="the_hub_slogan">
				<h1>News, Notes, Talk</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
		</a>
		
				<div class="the_hub_item">
			<div class="banner_img">
				<a href="https://lithub.com/patricia-lockwood-kiran-desai-ian-mcewan-and-more-24-new-books-out-today/" title="Patricia Lockwood, Kiran Desai, Ian McEwan, and more: 24 new books out today!">
		    		<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Screen-Shot-2025-09-18-at-3.25.24-PM.png" alt="" class="post_ft entry_post"/>
		    	</a>
			</div>
			
			<div class="post_content">
				<h1 data-report-url="/patricia-lockwood-kiran-desai-ian-mcewan-and-more-24-new-books-out-today/"><a href="https://lithub.com/patricia-lockwood-kiran-desai-ian-mcewan-and-more-24-new-books-out-today/">Patricia Lockwood, Kiran Desai, Ian McEwan, and more: 24 new books out today!</a></h1>
				
				<div class="author_info">
					<div class="author_photo"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/IMG_0692-1-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/IMG_0692-1-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Julia Hass" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></div>
					<div class="author_name">By&nbsp;<a href="https://lithub.com/author/juliahass/" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">Julia&nbsp;Hass</span></a></div>
					<div class="author_hr"><hr/></div>
					<div class="publish_date">September 23, 2025, 4:00am</div>
				</div>
				
				<p style="text-align: left;">Another week of hell in America. Dark times shade even darker, and yet through it all, in ways both uplifting and stupefying, life goes on. At the very least, be it for edification, or self-help, escapism, or grounding, books continue to be there for us.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">And this week, we welcome a hefty selection of new titles: Patricia Lockwood&#8217;s much anticipated novel on her experience with long Covid (amongst much else, too zany and myriad to get into here), Mona Awad&#8217;s sequel to <em>Bunny</em>, a new Ian McEwan novel, and a long awaited Kiran Desai novel. In nonfiction, we welcome a definitive biography of Muriel Spark, Kamala Harris&#8217;s obligatory campaign recap, a look at the genre of true crime, and a cultural history of &#8220;societal collapse&#8221; (timely). Me, I&#8217;ll be diving into Lockwood, Desai, and the Spark biography, but I believe there will be something for everyone in this week&#8217;s stack.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Happy reading!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255900" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/81658thcucl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81658THcucL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Patricia Lockwood, Will There Ever Be Another You" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81658THcucL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81658THcucL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-255900" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81658THcucL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" alt="Patricia Lockwood, Will There Ever Be Another You" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81658THcucL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81658THcucL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81658THcucL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81658THcucL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 662w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Patricia Lockwood, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593718551" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Will There Ever Be Another You</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Riverhead)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;So singular &#8230; Her ability to tease out the absurdity of ordinary communication is magnificent, even infuriating &#8230; Lockwood manages to explicate the harried, nonsensical, grief-soaked timeline with acrobatic skill.&#8221;<br />
â€”<em>The New Republic</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="259840" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/patricia-lockwood-kiran-desai-ian-mcewan-and-more-24-new-books-out-today/91iyyh9phyl-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/91iYyH9pHyL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Loneliness of Sonia and Sunny" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/91iYyH9pHyL._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/91iYyH9pHyL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-259840" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/91iYyH9pHyL._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" alt="" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/91iYyH9pHyL._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/91iYyH9pHyL._UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/91iYyH9pHyL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/91iYyH9pHyL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 658w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Kiran Desai, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780307700155" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Loneliness of Sonia and Sunny</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Hogarth)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Not so much a novel as a marvel &#8230; Here is sweet validation of the idea that to create something truly transcendent â€” a work of art depicting love, family, nature and culture in all their fullness â€” might take time.&#8221;<br />
â€”<em>The New York Times</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256502" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/9780593804728-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804728-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Ian McEwan,Â What We Can Know" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804728-copy-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804728-copy.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-256502" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804728-copy-199x300.jpg" alt="Ian McEwan,Â What We Can Know" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804728-copy-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804728-copy-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804728-copy-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780593804728-copy.jpg 662w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Ian McEwan, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593804728" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>What We Can Know</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Knopf)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;A philosophically charged tour de force by one of the best living novelists in English.&#8221;<br />
â€”<em>Kirkus</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255906" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/81pscaaggjl-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81pSCAAgGJL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Frances Wilson, Electric Spark: The Enigma of Dame Muriel" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81pSCAAgGJL._UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81pSCAAgGJL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-255906" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81pSCAAgGJL._UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" alt="Frances Wilson, Electric Spark: The Enigma of Dame Muriel" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81pSCAAgGJL._UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81pSCAAgGJL._UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81pSCAAgGJL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81pSCAAgGJL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 667w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Frances Wilson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780374613204" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Electric Spark: The Enigma of Dame Muriel</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(FSG)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Frances Wilson revels in her sublimely contrary subject &#8230; Wilson borrows Sparkâ€™s own mystical whimsy about the relationship between her life and her work.â€<br />
â€”<em>The Atlantic</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="259759" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/?attachment_id=259759" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1696,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="we love you, bunny" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-678x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-259759" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-199x300.jpg" alt="we love you, bunny" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-1017x1536.jpg 1017w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-1356x2048.jpg 1356w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Awad-Cover-Art-scaled.jpg 1696w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Mona Awad, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781668059869" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>We Love You, Bunny</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Marysue Rucci)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;[A] dark, twisted satire of academia and the cultlike world of writers.&#8221;<br />
