<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;One of the most insightful books Iâ€™ve read about what makes us human and how we understand each other. It changed how I think about the interactions I have, and I bet it will do the same for you.â€<br />
â€”Bill Gates</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="259859" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/patricia-lockwood-kiran-desai-ian-mcewan-and-more-24-new-books-out-today/81g2mormrll-_uf350350_ql50_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/81g2MoRmrLL._UF350350_QL50_.jpg" data-orig-size="221,350" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Amanda, HS Cross" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/81g2MoRmrLL._UF350350_QL50_-189x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/81g2MoRmrLL._UF350350_QL50_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-259859" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/81g2MoRmrLL._UF350350_QL50_-189x300.jpg" alt="Amanda, HS Cross" width="189" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/81g2MoRmrLL._UF350350_QL50_-189x300.jpg 189w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/81g2MoRmrLL._UF350350_QL50_-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/81g2MoRmrLL._UF350350_QL50_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/81g2MoRmrLL._UF350350_QL50_.jpg 221w" sizes="(max-width: 189px) 100vw, 189px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>H S Cross, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9798889661351" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Amanda</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Europa)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;About two lovers driven apart by secrets and brought together again by irrepressible need &#8230; A scintillating historical novel about the potential revival of a star-crossed love.&#8221;<br />
â€”<em>Foreword Reviews</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="259860" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/patricia-lockwood-kiran-desai-ian-mcewan-and-more-24-new-books-out-today/9781324094975_300/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781324094975_300.jpeg" data-orig-size="300,451" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="On Drugs, Justin Smith" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781324094975_300-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781324094975_300.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-259860" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781324094975_300-200x300.jpeg" alt="On Drugs, Justin Smith" width="200" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781324094975_300-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781324094975_300-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781324094975_300-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9781324094975_300.jpeg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Justin Smith-Ruiu, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781324094975" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>On Drugs: Psychedelics, Philosophy, and the Nature of Reality</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Liveright)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">â€œAn insightful work of philosophy supported by a surprisingly powerful memoiristic arc, Justin Smith-Ruiu&#8217;s new book works better than any psychedelic could to reopen the doors of perception and cast humanity&#8217;s long-standing hunger for mind-altering experiences in a new and thrilling light.&#8221;<br />
â€”Kristen Roupenian</p>
